quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  58,7,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not seen that Allah knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth? There is no secret conversation between three but He is their fourth, nor between five but He is their sixth, nor less than <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…nor less than that, nor (is there) more but He is with them…”</span>
  58,8,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not seen those who were prohibited from conversing secretly but then revert to what they were prohibited from? They <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza and Roways read it as: “…they converse with one another secretly in sin…”</span>
  58,9,"O you who have attained faith, when you converse secretly, do not <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Roways read it as: “…do not converse with one another secretly in sin…”</span>
  58,10,"Indeed,<i class=""s"">(malicious) </i>private conversations are from Satan, <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’ read it as: “…that he may make those who have attained faith sad.”</span>